</div></figure>



<p>Besides, I also did the QR code page, in which people will scan the QR code to answer some questions and get assigned their role number for the poem reading. It was also my first time using WebSocket to transfer data. To enhance security and prevent external interference, I implemented session IDs to ensure each session had a unique URL.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo span2"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<div style="--width:960; --height:556;"><img decoding="async" style="--twidth:960; --theight:556;" alt="thumbnail" src="" data-src="https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/1852900545-369e11cf2f9ccb138a915e8c80a147a53edbb2e2e4b7121acb9ba6baece7f228-d_960" data-srcset="" srcset=""><iframe title="Karaoke Poetry Web Socket" src="" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write" data-src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/946697218?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963"></iframe></div>
</div></figure>



<p><strong>2. Souvenirs</strong><br><strong><br></strong><em>A location-based AR experience at Fort Canning Park. This experience invites people to explore Fort Canning Park and uncover hidden AR secrets along the way!</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large vertical" style="--width:516; --height:1024;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="516" height="1024" src="" alt="" class="wp-image-258" srcset="" sizes="(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px" data-src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-13-516x1024.png" data-srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-13-516x1024.png 516w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-13-151x300.png 151w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-13-768x1523.png 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-13-774x1536.png 774w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-13.png 846w"></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large vertical" style="--width:516; --height:1024;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="516" height="1024" src="" alt="" class="wp-image-259" srcset="" sizes="(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px" data-src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-14-516x1024.png" data-srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-14-516x1024.png 516w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-14-151x300.png 151w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-14-768x1523.png 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-14-774x1536.png 774w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-14.png 846w"></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large vertical" style="--width:516; --height:1024;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="516" height="1024" src="" alt="" class="wp-image-260" srcset="" sizes="(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px" data-src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-15-516x1024.png" data-srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-15-516x1024.png 516w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-15-151x300.png 151w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-15-768x1523.png 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-15-774x1536.png 774w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-15.png 846w"></figure>



<p>One of the interesting thing I did was creating this raindrop scene that changes based on the user&rsquo;s camera angle. When the camera points toward the sky, raindrops appear on the screen gradually.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
